Two members of One Direction are being forced to post bonds worth nearly £6,600 to be allowed into the Philippines following a video which allegedly saw them smoking marijuana.

Zayn Malik and Louis Tomlinson are required to put down the money ahead of One Direction's concert in Manila this weekend, to be forfeited if they are caught using, or impliedly promoting, illegal drugs while in the Philippines.

This comes in the wake of a video filmed last April, where the pair were seen joking about drugs as they appeared to share a roll-up 'joint' during the Latin America leg of their 2014 Stadium Tour.

